{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Ally Toast Notifications\n      When a spawned CC or pi session reports in via sending stone, a small toast slides in from the bottom-right with the ally name and message preview. Click to jump to that session. Keeps you aware of ally activity without leaving Ember's stream.","choice":"ally-toasts","id":null,"timestamp":1776095330029}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Panel Drawer (Right Side)\n      The state panel becomes a collapsible drawer. Click a tab icon to expand it wider and show richer panels — dragon-guard permissions, kobold task board, memory vault browser. Collapsed by default so the thought stream stays wide. Foundation for sub-project 3.","choice":"panel-drawer","id":null,"timestamp":1776095333598}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Command Palette (Ctrl+K)\n      Quick fuzzy-search overlay for switching sessions, opening panels, jumping to settings, running daemon commands. Same muscle memory as VS Code / Raycast. Keeps the chrome minimal while everything stays one shortcut away.","choice":"command-palette","id":null,"timestamp":1776095344777}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"D\n    \n      Thought Stream Filters\n      Toggle buttons in the stream header to show/hide event types: think, speak, observe, beat. When Ember gets chatty during a long thought cycle, you can filter down to just speak events to see what she actually said vs. her inner monologue.","choice":"thought-filters","id":null,"timestamp":1776095358897}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"E\n    \n      Theme System\n      Dark by default (as shown), but with a theme system that can be swapped. Not just light/dark — let personas influence the color accent. Ember gets warm amber, Maren gets her own palette. The active persona tints the UI.","choice":"dark-theme-toggle","id":null,"timestamp":1776095360486}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"F\n    \n      Connection Health Bar\n      Thin strip at the top showing SSE connection status per persona — connected (green dot), reconnecting (amber pulse), disconnected (red). Since psi talks to multiple doggy ports, you need to see at a glance which daemons are alive. Auto-reconnect with backoff.","choice":"connection-status","id":null,"timestamp":1776095365660}
{"type":"screen-added","file":"/home/dot/Development/hoard/.superpowers/brainstorm/166102-1776095095/content/panels-overview.html"}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"Q\n    \n      Quest Board\n      Live view of dispatched allies — which quests are running, who's working on what, status updates from sending stone check-ins. The kobold-housekeeping task board + quest status combined. Shows ally taxonomy (scout/coder/reviewer/researcher/planner) with colored badges.","choice":"quest-board","id":null,"timestamp":1776095513883}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"G\n    \n      Dragon Guard\n      Permission tier display and tool-call audit log. Shows current permission level (Dog/Puppy/Ally/Dragon), recent tool calls with approve/deny status, and lets you promote or restrict sessions. The safety dashboard.","choice":"dragon-guard","id":null,"timestamp":1776095561959}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"M\n    \n      Memory Vault\n      Browse, search, and edit the daemon's memory. Shelves organized by type (observations, decisions, dot-context). Each entry shows timestamp, source session, and content. Private shelf entries flagged with a lock icon. Direct write/delete from here.","choice":"memory-vault","id":null,"timestamp":1776095572948}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"X\n    \n      Context Inspector\n      View and edit CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, rules files, and persona YAML. Tree view of all context files across the hoard. Inline editor with save. See what context each session is carrying — like claude-crusts but integrated into psi.","choice":"context-inspector","id":null,"timestamp":1776095582878}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      Attention Monitor\n      Rich attention state beyond the sidebar gauge. Historical graph of attention over time, cost breakdown per tool type, regen rate visualization, rest gate schedule. See when the daemon is spending vs. recovering attention.","choice":"attention-monitor","id":null,"timestamp":1776095594729}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"L\n    \n      Session Log\n      Scrollable history of all daemon sessions — past thought cycles, tool invocations, memory writes. Searchable. Filter by date, event type, body source. The dragon-scroll equivalent: full audit trail of everything the daemon has done.","choice":"session-log","id":null,"timestamp":1776095654955}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"S\n    \n      Settings\n      Daemon configuration editor — persona selection, LLM provider settings, attention pool tuning, body toggles, contract management, psi interface ports. Edit the YAML visually instead of by hand. Restart daemon with new config from here.","choice":"settings","id":null,"timestamp":1776095667114}
